Title: 
 A Nonparametric Model of Term Structure Dynamics and the Market Price of Interest Rate Risk.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1973-2002
Issue: 5
Volume: 52
Year: 1997
Month:  December 
Abstract:

 This article presents a technique for nonparametrically estimating
 continuous-time diffusion processes that are observed at discrete
 intervals. The authors illustrate the methodology by using daily three and
 six month Treasury bill data, from January 1965 to July 1995, to estimate
 the drift and diffusion of the short rate, and the market price of
 interest rate risk. While the estimated diffusion is similar to that
 estimated by K. C. Chan, et al.(1992), there is evidence of substantial
 nonlinearity in the drift. This is close to zero for low and medium
 interest rates but mean reversion increases sharply at higher interest
 rates.


