Title: 
 An Anatomy of the "S&P Game": The Effects of Changing the Rules.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1909-30
Issue: 5
Volume: 51
Year: 1996
Month:  December 
Abstract:

 This study analyzes the effects of changes in S&P 500 index composition
 from January 1986 through June 1994, a period during which Standard and
 Poor's began its practice of preannouncing changes five days beforehand.
 The new announcement practice has given rise to the 'S&P game' and has
 altered the way stock prices react. The authors find that prices increase
 abnormally from the close on the announcement day to the close on the
 effective day. The overall increase is greater than under the old
 announcement policy, although part of the increase reverses after the
 stock is included in the index.


