Title: 
 The Delisting Bias in CRSP Data.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 327-40
Issue: 1
Volume: 52
Year: 1997
Month:  March 
Abstract:

 The author documents a delisting bias in the stock return data base
 maintained by the Center for Research in Security Prices. He finds that
 delists for bankruptcy and other negative reasons are generally surprises
 and that correct delisting returns are not available for most of the
 stocks that have been delisted for negative reasons since 1962. Using
 over-the-counter price data, the author shows that the omitted delisting
 returns are large. Implications of the bias are discussed.


