Author-Name: 
  Brown, David P
Author-Name:  Zhang, Zhi Ming
Title: 
 Market Orders and Market Efficiency.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 277-308
Issue: 1
Volume: 52
Year: 1997
Month:  March 
Abstract:

 This work compares a dealer market and a limit-order book. Dealers
 commonly observe order flow and collect information from multiple market
 orders. They may be better informed than other traders, although they do
 not earn rents from this information. Dealers earn rents as suppliers of
 liquidity and their decisions to enter or exit the market are independent
 of the degree of adverse selection. Introduction of a limit-order book
 lowers the execution-price risk faced by speculators and leads them to
 trade more aggressively on their information. Introduction of the book
 also lowers dealer profits but increases the informational efficiency of
 prices.


