Title: 
 Equilibrium Valuation of Foreign Exchange Claims.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 799-826
Issue: 2
Volume: 52
Year: 1997
Month:  June 
Abstract:

 This article studies the equilibrium valuation of foreign exchange
 contingent claims. Within a continuous-time Lucas (1982) two-country
 model, exchange rates, interest rates, and, in particular, factor risk
 prices are all endogenously and jointly determined. This guarantees the
 internal consistency of these price processes with a general equilibrium.
 In the same model, closed-form valuation formulas are presented for
 currency options and currency futures options. Common to these formulas is
 that stochastic volatility and stochastic interest rates are admitted.
 Hedge ratios and other comparative statics are also provided analytically.
 It is shown that most existing currency option models are included as
 special cases.


