Title: 
 Strategic Debt Service.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 531-56
Issue: 2
Volume: 52
Year: 1997
Month:  June 
Abstract:

 When firms experience financial distress, equity holders may act
 strategically, forcing concessions from debtholders and paying less than
 the originally contracted interest payments. This article incorporates
 strategic debt service in a standard, continuous time asset pricing model,
 developing simple closed-form expressions for debt and equity values. The
 authors find that strategic debt service can account for a substantial
 proportion of the premium on risky corporate debt. They analyze the
 efficiency implications of strategic debt service, showing that it can
 eliminate both direct bankruptcy costs and agency costs of debt.


