Title: 
 Informed Traders, Intervention, and Price Leadership: A Deeper View of the Microstructure of the Foreign Exchange Market.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1589-1614
Issue: 4
Volume: 52
Year: 1997
Month:  September 
Abstract:

 This article identifies price leadership patterns in foreign exchange
 trading, with a focus on central bank intervention as an informational
 trigger for leadership positioning. Granger causality tests applied to
 DM/US$ spot rate quotes reveal Deutsche Bank as a price leader up to sixty
 minutes prior to Bundesbank interventionary reports. By the minus
 twenty-five-minute mark, interbank quote adjustments become two-way
 Granger-causal. These results suggest that central bank activity is
 revealed in stages: first to the price leader, then to competitors, and
 lastly to the general public.


