Title: 
 Portfolio Disclosures and Year-End Price Shifts.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1563-88
Issue: 4
Volume: 52
Year: 1997
Month:  September 
Abstract:

 Commercial paper sells at an extra discount if it matures in the next
 calendar year but Treasury bills do not. The discount is apparent in
 downward price shifts before the year-end, and upward price shifts at the
 turn of the year that are significantly correlated with the simultaneous
 returns to small stocks, and that cannot reflect tax-loss selling.
 Cross-sectional and time-series tests on prices, as well as flow of funds
 evidence on trades by institutional investors, indicate that both the debt
 and equity patterns reflect agency problems related to portfolio
 disclosures.


