Issue: 3
Volume: 51
Year: 1996
Month:  July 
Abstract:

 This article explores the fundamental factors that affect cross-country
 stock return correlations. Using transactions data from 1988 to 1992, the
 authors construct overnight and intraday returns for a portfolio of
 Japanese stocks using their NYSE-traded American depository receipts and a
 matched-sample portfolio of U.S. stocks. They find that U.S. macroeconomic
 announcements, shocks to the yen/dollar foreign exchange rate and Treasury
 bill returns, and industry effects have no measurable influence on U.S.
