 significantly decline during the same periods. Their results suggest that
 the directional change in the total bid-ask spread depends on the relative
 magnitudes of the changes in these three components. Specifically, the
 decreases in inventory holding costs and order processing costs imply that
 earnings announcements may have an insignificant impact on the total
 bid-ask spread, even when they result in increased information asymmetry.

