Title: 
 Evidence of Bank Market Discipline in Subordinated Debenture Yields: 1983-1991.

Journal: Journal of Finance
Pages: 1347-77
Issue: 4
Volume: 51
Year: 1996
Month:  September 
Abstract:

 The authors examine debenture yields over the period 1983-91 to evaluate
 the market's sensitivity to bank-specific risks and conclude that
 investors have rationally reflected changes in the government's policy
 toward absorbing private losses in the event of a bank failure. Although
 this evidence does not establish that market discipline can effectively
 control banking firms, it soundly rejects the hypothesis that investors
 cannot rationally differentiate among the risks undertaken by the major
 U.S. banking firms.


